  "prompt": "Did any of Melania Trump's family come to her wedding? Did anyone \"give her away?\" And who paid for her wedding gown?",
  "response": "Melania Trump\u2019s wedding to Donald Trump took place on January 22, 2005, at the Bethesda-by-the-Sea Episcopal Church in Palm Beach, Florida. Her family, including her parents, Viktor and Amalija Knavs, attended the wedding, with her father walking her down the aisle. Regarding the wedding gown, Melania wore a custom-designed dress by John Galliano for Dior. While the specifics of who paid for the gown are not publicly detailed, it is generally assumed that it was covered as part of the wedding expenses, often by the couple themselves or their families.",
